At least three persons have been killed by flood while 500 were displaced in Bosso and Chanchaga Local Government Areas of Niger State. The incident was said to have occurred yesterday following a heavy rainfall. Witnesses said the flood submerged more than 20 houses and destroyed other buildings, including shops. The acting governor, Muhammad Ahmed Ketso, who visited the area, directed the State Emergency Management Agency (NSEMA) to immediately take inventory of losses and provide relief materials comprising of food and non-food items to cushion victimsâ€™ hardship. He further called on the federal government and relevant bodies to assist the state in addressing the unending disaster caused by flood annually. JUST IN: Flood kills 3, displaces 500 in Niger How flood is wreaking havoc on states Flood displaces 53,000 persons in Kogi, Niger Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin